      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Prioritizing debt reduction first is the fiscally conservative choice, as runaway debt guarantees future economic crises. If the government is consistently spending beyond its means, the market will lose confidence, leading to higher interest rates that make the debt even harder to manage. However, ignoring social safety nets entirely while cutting spending can lead to massive social instability, which ultimately costs the economy far more than timely social investment.",
      "source": "target",
