    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but you're saying fixing the math comes second to spending? that feels like you're basically saying we should just keep borrowing more to pay for things now, even if it ruins things for the next generation. isn't it actually more \"responsible\" to stop the bleeding first? why does it seem like you're making excuses for ignoring the debt?",
